>>36185636
I think >>36185715 has a good outlook, but you may find that some difficult scenes are necessary to flesh out due to foreshadowing, or character development. "Anticlimactic" is a valid criticism because when a climax is resolved in a way that doesn't match the tone of the rest of the work (or in this case, abridged completely), it robs the reader of catharsis. Abridging any important scene can do this.
I'll use an example in my own work by spoiling my next update. One of my characters has been holding a pretty important secret from the love interest, one that could completely change the dynamics of their relationship and force her to see him in a new light. I've developed my characters enough to foreshadow a really nasty confrontation when that secret finally comes to light. It's very important that I take the time and effort to flesh out that scene well, because it's crucial for the development of both characters, for the continuation of the plot, and for the reader's catharsis.
Anonymous
